  "prompt": "Why is it harder to stay married than to divorce?",
  "response": "Staying married can be challenging for several reasons:\n\n1. Personal growth and change\n- People evolve over time\n- Differing life goals and expectations\n- Individual personalities and needs shift\n\n2. Communication challenges\n- Difficulty expressing feelings\n- Unresolved conflicts\n- Poor listening skills\n\n3. External stressors\n- Financial pressures\n- Work-related stress\n- Family and social challenges\n\n4. Emotional complexity\n- Maintaining intimacy and connection\n- Sustaining romantic feelings\n- Managing expectations\n\n5. Easier alternatives\n- Divorce is more socially acceptable now\n- Individual independence is valued\n- Less social stigma around separation\n\n6. Effort and commitment required\n- Continuous relationship maintenance\n- Willingness to compromise\n- Working through difficulties together\n\n7. Emotional and practical complications\n- Potential impact on children\n- Financial implications\n- Emotional investment\n\nDivorce might seem easier because it offers a seemingly quick solution to complex relationship problems. However, successful marriages require ongoing mutual effort, understanding, and commitment from both partners.\n\nNote: These are general observations and individual experiences vary significantly.",
